  "prompt": "Why did Hillary Clinton lie under oath about her emails?",
  "response": "Hillary Clinton has faced significant scrutiny regarding her use of a private email server during her tenure as Secretary of State. However, whether she intentionally lied under oath has been a matter of debate among her supporters and critics.\n\nThe controversy primarily stems from her statements regarding the nature and handling of her emails. Critics allege that she made false statements in her testimony, particularly regarding her understanding of classified information and her actions related to email deletion. Clinton and her representatives have maintained that she did not intentionally mislead anyone and that her use of a private server was permissible under the rules at the time. \n\nIn 2016, the FBI investigated her handling of classified information and concluded that while her actions were \"extremely careless,\" there was no sufficient evidence to recommend criminal charges. Ultimately, discussions around her emails were highly politicized, contributing to the complex narrative surrounding the issue.\n\nIt's important to consider this issue from multiple perspectives, as interpretations of her actions can vary widely based on political views and interpretations of the facts.",
